# Go conventions

## Engine & store

- Business logic lives in `internal/engine`; HTTP stays thin in `internal/api`
- Pass `context.Context` through; use `Store.WithTx` for atomic multi-write paths
- `CompleteTask` checks activity is active `userTask`; does not validate assignee identity

## Adding persistence

1. Extend `engine.Store` in `internal/engine/store.go`
2. Implement in `internal/store/memory/store.go` (tests)
3. Implement in `internal/store/gormstore/store.go`
4. Implement in `internal/store/filestore/store.go` (delegates to memory + YAML persist)

## Tests

- Engine tests: `memstore.NewStore()` + `engine.NewEngine(store, nil)`
- Table-driven tests preferred; run `go test ./internal/engine/... ./internal/bpmn/...`

## Scripts

- `internal/script`: `scriptLang` `js` (default) or `log`; JS exposes `http.get/post/request`
- Do not expose unrestricted network/file access in scripts without explicit security review
